body.p:
The following example shows how to securely load data into an external table. The example creates a readable external table named ext_expenses from all files with the txt extension, using the gpfdists protocol. The files are formatted with a pipe (|) as the column delimiter and an empty space as null.
Run gpfdist with the --ssl option on the segment hosts.
Log into the database and execute the following command: =# CREATE EXTERNAL TABLE ext_expenses ( name text, date date, amount float4, category text, desc1 text ) LOCATION ('gpfdists://etlhost-1:8081/*.txt', 'gpfdists://etlhost-2:8082/*.txt') FORMAT 'TEXT' ( DELIMITER '|' NULL ' ') ;

ol.li:
Create a table called userssn and insert some sensitive data, social security numbers for Bob and Alice, in this example. Paste the public.key contents after "dearmor(". CREATE TABLE userssn( ssn_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY, username varchar(100), ssn bytea);
